
[1]hirsute

   HIRSU'TE, a. [L. hirsutus.]

   1. Hairy; rough with hair; shaggy; set with bristles.

   2. In botany, it is nearly synonymous with hispid, but it denotes
   having more hairs or bristles, and less stiff.
